i\u201d Crespo, 13 [[Ferran Mart\u00ednez]], 14 [[Antonio Mart\u00edn Espina]], 15 [[Juan Antonio San Epifanio|Juan Antonio \"Epi\" San Epifanio]] (Coach: [[Lolo Sainz]])\n----\n'''[[1994 FIBA World Championship|1994 FIBA World Cup]]:''' finished '''10th''' among 16 teams\n\n4 [[Andr\u00e9s Jim\u00e9nez (basketball)|Andr\u00e9s Jim\u00e9nez]], 5 [[Enrique Andreu]], 6 [[Alberto Herreros]], 7 Jos\u00e9 Cargol, 8 [[Ferran Mart\u00ednez]], 9 [[Juan Antonio Orenga]], 10 [[Jos\u00e9 Miguel Ant\u00fanez]], 11 [[Rafael Vecina]], 12 [[Rafael Jofresa]], 13 [[Pablo Laso]], 14 [[Juan Antonio San Epifanio|Juan Antonio \"Epi\" San Epifanio]], 15 [[Jordi Villacampa]] (Coach: [[Lolo Sainz]])\n----\n'''[[1995 EuroBasket]]:''' finished '''6th''' among 14 teams\n\n4 [[Alberto Angulo]], 5 [[:es:Jos\u00e9 Luis Galilea|Jos\u00e9 Luis Galilea]], 6 [[Mike Smith (basketball, born 1963)|Mike Smith]], 7 [[Juan Antonio Orenga]], 8 [[Ignacio Rodr\u00edguez]], 9 [[Pablo Laso]], 10 [[Xavi Fern\u00e1ndez]], 11 [[Alberto Herreros]], 12 [[Alfonso Reyes (basketball)|Alfonso Reyes]], 13 [[Ferran Mart\u00ednez]], 14 [[Antonio Mart\u00edn Espina]], 15 [[:es:Fran Murcia|Fran Murcia]] (Coach: [[Lolo Sainz]])\n----\n'''[[1997 EuroBasket]]:''' finished '''5th''' among 16 teams\n\n4 [[Alberto Angulo]], 5 Jos\u00e9 Luis Galilea, 6 [[Tom\u00e1s Jofresa]], 7 [[Juan Antonio Orenga]], 8 [[Ignacio Rodr\u00edguez]], 9 [[Mike Smith (basketball, born 1963)|Mike Smith]], 10 [[:es:Roger Esteller|Roger Esteller]], 11 [[Alberto Herreros]], 12 [[:es:Jos\u00e9 Antonio Para\u00edso|Jos\u00e9 Antonio Para\u00edso]], 13 [[Ferran Mart\u00ednez]], 14 [[Alfonso Reyes (basketball)|Alfonso Reyes]], 15 [[Roberto Due\u00f1as]] (Coach: [[Lolo Sainz]])\n----\n'''[[1998 FIBA World Championship|1998 FIBA World Cup]]:''' finished '''5th''' among 16 teams\n\n4 [[Alberto Angulo]], 5 [[Nacho Rodilla]], 6 [[Nacho Azofra]], 7 [[Juan Antonio Orenga]], 8 [[Ignacio Rodr\u00edguez]], 9 [[Carlos Jim\u00e9nez]], 10 [[Rodrigo De la Fuente]], 11 [[Al